content.text:
I now have a thorough understanding of the entire onboarding flow. Let me summarize what I've found and present the comprehensive implementation plan.

---

## Implementation Plan: Onboarding Flow Design Harmonization

### Summary of Current State

There are **two separate profile editor implementations**:

1. **Onboarding Profile Editor** (first-time setup) -- rendered inline in `C:\Users\johnm\iskrib_v3\client\src\components\HomePage\Home.jsx` (lines 443-523), styled by `C:\Users\johnm\iskrib_v3\client\src\components\HomePage\home.css` (lines 96-251). This is the one shown when `checkUser` returns `exist: false`. It has the cold navy `rgb(4, 20, 29)` background, hardcoded white text, no CSS variables.

2. **Profile Edit Modal** (returning users) -- in `C:\Users\johnm\iskrib_v3\client\src\components\ProfilePage\components\ProfileEditModal.jsx`, styled by `C:\Users\johnm\iskrib_v3\client\src\components\ProfilePage\myprofile.css`. This one already uses CSS variables (`var(--bg-elevated)`, `var(--text-primary)`, etc.) and is mostly consistent with the design system. This component does NOT need major changes.

3. **Welcome Message** -- `C:\Users\johnm\iskrib_v3\client\src\components\WelcomeMessage\WelcomeMessage.jsx` + `welcomemessage.css`. Hardcoded white, generic party popper SVG, no CTA, duplicate media queries.

The onboarding flow is: Signup (beautiful editorial design) -> checkUser() finds no profile -> **Onboarding Profile Editor** (cold dark navy) -> submit -> **Welcome Message** (plain white card).

---

### Change 1: Harmonize the Onboarding Profile Editor

**Files to modify:**
- `C:\Users\johnm\iskrib_v3\client\src\components\HomePage\home.css` (CSS overhaul of the profile editor section)
- `C:\Users\johnm\iskrib_v3\client\src\components\HomePage\Home.jsx` (JSX updates for better copy, structure, and username feedback)

#### CSS Changes in `home.css` (lines 96-251)

**Replace `.profile-editor-bg`** (line 96-106):
```css
/* BEFORE */
.profile-editor-bg{
    background-color: rgba(141, 141, 141, 0.2);
    /* ... */
}

/* AFTER — match the warm backdrop used elsewhere */
.profile-editor-bg{
    position: absolute;
    display: flex;
    justify-content: center;
    align-items: center;
    background-color: var(--bg-backdrop-heavy);
    backdrop-filter: blur(8px);
    -webkit-backdrop-filter: blur(8px);
    width: 100%;
    height: 100vh;
    z-index: 140;
}
```
**Rationale:** Uses the same `--bg-backdrop-heavy` token that the rest of the app uses for modal overlays (e.g., profile page loading container at `myprofile.css` line 6). The warm cream-tinted backdrop replaces the cold gray.

**Replace `.profile-editor`** (line 107-116):
```css
/* BEFORE */
.profile-editor{
    background-color: rgb(4, 20, 29); /* cold navy — the core problem */
    width: 50%;
    height: 90%;
    /* ... */
}

/* AFTER — warm editorial card that mirrors the signup form card */
.profile-editor{
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    align-items: flex-start;
    border-radius: 16px;
    width: 100%;
    max-width: 440px;
    height: auto;
    max-height: 90vh;
    overflow-y: auto;
    background-color: var(--bg-card);
    border: 1px solid var(--border-card);
    box-shadow: var(--shadow-modal);
    padding: 36px 32px 28px;
    z-index: 140;
    animation: slideUp 0.4s cubic-bezier(0.16, 1, 0.3, 1) both;
}
```
**Rationale:** Mirrors the `auth-form-card` from signup.css: `max-width: 440px`, `var(--bg-card)`, `var(--border-card)`, `var(--shadow-modal)`, same `slideUp` animation. Changes from fixed 50%/90% dimensions to a centered max-width card that grows with content. The `@keyframes slideUp` already exists in signup.css and can be duplicated here (or moved to index.css if preferred).

**Replace `.edit-profile-header`** (line 117-123):
```css
.edit-profile-header{
    display: flex;
    justify-content: space-between;
    align-items: center;
    width: 100%;
    margin-bottom: 24px;
}
```

**Replace `.edit-profile-title-container`** (line 124-128):
```css
/* BEFORE */
.edit-profile-title-container{
    font-size: 1.4rem;
    font-weight: 650;
    margin-left: 1.5rem;
}

/* AFTER — uses Playfair Display, matches signup .form-title */
.edit-profile-title-container{
    font-family: "Playfair Display", serif;
    font-size: 1.5rem;
    font-weight: 600;
    letter-spacing: -0.02em;
    color: var(--text-heading);
}
```
**Rationale:** Directly mirrors the `.form-title` class from signup.css (line 174-181).

**Replace `.save-bttn` and `.save-bttn-disabled`** (lines 129-155):
```css
/* BEFORE — white on navy, no transitions, disabled is just gray */
.save-bttn{
    color: rgb(4, 20, 29);
    background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);
}

/* AFTER — gold accent button matching auth primary-button style */
.save-bttn{
    display: inline-flex;
    justify-content: center;
    align-items: center;
    padding: 10px 24px;
    border-radius: 8px;
    border: none;
    background: var(--accent-dark);
    color: var(--bg-primary);
    font-family: var(--font-ui);
    font-size: 0.88rem;
    font-weight: 600;
    letter-spacing: 0.02em;
    cursor: pointer;
    transition: transform 0.15s ease, box-shadow 0.2s ease, background-color 0.2s ease;
    box-shadow: 0 2px 8px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.08);
}
.save-bttn:hover{
    transform: translateY(-1px);
    box-shadow: 0 4px 16px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.12);
}
.save-bttn:active{
    transform: translateY(0);
}

.save-bttn-disabled{
    display: inline-flex;
    justify-content: center;
    align-items: center;
    padding: 10px 24px;
    border-radius: 8px;
    border: none;
    background: var(--accent-dark);
    color: var(--bg-primary);
    font-family: var(--font-ui);
    font-size: 0.88rem;
    font-weight: 600;
    opacity: 0.4;
    cursor: not-allowed;
    box-shadow: none;
}
```
**Rationale:** Matches the `.primary-button` / `.primary-button:disabled` pattern from signup.css.

**Replace `.profile-edit-container`** (line 156-162):
```css
/* BEFORE */
.profile-edit-container{
    background-color: rgb(4, 20, 29); /* hardcoded navy — remove */
}

/* AFTER */
.profile-edit-container{
    position: relative;
    display: flex;
    height: fit-content;
    width: 100%;
    margin-bottom: 8px;
}
```

**Replace `.profile-edit-backdrop-filter`** (line 163-173):
```css
.profile-edit-backdrop-filter{
    position: absolute;
    display: flex;
    justify-content: center;
    align-items: center;
    width: 100px;
    height: 100px;
    border-radius: 50%;
    background-color: var(--bg-overlay);
    backdrop-filter: blur(4px);
    -webkit-backdrop-filter: blur(4px);
    z-index: 2;
    cursor: pointer;
    opacity: 0;
    transition: opacity 0.2s ease;
}
.profile-edit-container:hover .profile-edit-backdrop-filter{
    opacity: 1;
}
```

**Replace `.input-title`** (line 205-207):
```css
/* BEFORE */
.input-title{
    color: rgba(151, 151, 151, 0.882); /* hardcoded gray */
}

/* AFTER */
.input-title{
    font-family: var(--font-ui);
    font-size: 0.7rem;
    font-weight: 600;
    color: var(--text-muted);
    letter-spacing: 0.12em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
}
```
**Rationale:** Mirrors `.form-field label` from signup.css (line 205-212).

**Replace `.name-input-container` and `.bio-input-container`** (lines 208-235):
```css
.name-input-container{
    display: flex;
    width: 100%;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 6px;
}

.bio-input-container{
    display: flex;
    width: 100%;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 6px;
}
```

**Replace `.edit-profile-name-input` and `.edit-profile-bio-input`** (lines 218-245):
```css
.edit-profile-name-input{
    font-family: var(--font-ui);
    width: 100%;
    border: 1px solid var(--border-card);
    background: var(--bg-primary);
    padding: 12px 14px;
    border-radius: 8px;
    font-size: 0.95rem;
